h3. Notes

Looking at JSON page: https://<EXAMPLE>.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/spacedirectory/1/search?query=&type=personal&status=current&pageSize=24&startIndex=0

1 user had a missing value for avatar image. 

{code}
"logo": {
    "href": "/wiki/download/attachments/13206209/user-avatar",
    "type": "image/png",
    "rel": "logo"
},
{code}

Avatar image is what is used for Personal Space logo. Since the logo was causing the error selecting "All Spaces" was not loading.

h3. Probable Workaround
_there are a few reports that this workaround was not successful_

# Use Development browser tools to confirm his error: 
{code}
com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-space-directory:space-directory.js?locale=en-GB:9 Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'href' of undefined
{code}
# Pull up site JSON: https://<EXAMPLE>.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/spacedirectory/1/search?query=&type=personal&status=current&pageSize=24&startIndex=0
# Find the user where the href for the user is not a defined path. Example: 
{code}
    "href": "/wiki/download/attachments/13206209/user-avatar",
{code}
# Log into Confluence. 
# Navigated to user's profile. 
# Download the profile image and save locally. 
# Rename image. Make sure there are *no* spaces or odd characters.
# Effect should be immediate. Check All space link to make sure Spaces now load.

