Workaround:
Do not expand the metadata labels

*Steps to reproduce*
Using Chrome latest version available ( Version 41.0.2272.104 (64-bit))
# Create a Confluence page with text that exceeds the screen size;
# In the page editor view, click on Search;
# Search for any word within the text;

*Expected behavior*
Confluence should points the location of the highlighted word and it should appear on Chrome directly to the user.

*Actual behavior*
Although the word is highlighted, the browser does not scroll down to point the word location, the user has to search for the highlighted word instead.

