Onscreen error when attempting to create a new page from broken blueprint:
!Blueprint Error.png|thumbnail!
 
h3. Notes
Checking DB, the error references a TEMPLATE_ID that does not exist:
{noformat}confluence_1399351=> select "ID", "NAME", "PLUGIN_MODULE_KEY", "TEMPLATE_ID" from "AO_54C900_C_TEMPLATE_REF" where "NAME" like '%retrospective%' and "TEMPLATE_ID" <> 0;
 ID |             NAME              |                                  PLUGIN_MODULE_KEY                                  | TEMPLATE_ID
----+-------------------------------+-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------
 46 | retrospectives.blueprint.name | com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-software-blueprints:retrospectives-page |     5177345
(1 row){noformat}

h3. Check for the multiple versions of the TEMPLATE_ID
{noformat}confluence_1399351=> select templateid, templatename, modulekey, prevver, version from pagetemplates where modulekey like '%retrospective%';
 templateid | templatename  |      modulekey      | prevver | version
------------+---------------+---------------------+---------+---------
     704901 | Retrospective | retrospectives-page |         |       2
     704903 | Retrospective | retrospectives-page |  704901 |       1
(2 rows){noformat}

h3.Workaround
Manually update TEMPLATE_ID in the "AO_54C900_C_TEMPLATE_REF" table to one that exists within pagetemplates.
If multiple versions are available, the highest version number; it should be the one that does not have a "prevver" 

For Example:
{noformat}update "AO_54C900_C_TEMPLATE_REF" set "TEMPLATE_ID" = 704901 where "ID" = 46;{noformat}

h3. Summary
By using a code like this:
{code}
{livesearch:spaceKey=exp}
{code}
In the "Look and Feel > Sidebar, header and footer > Sidebar" of a Space, it's possible to enable the Livesearch macro to appear in the sidebar of Confluence for this particular Space.

However, the behaviour exhibited by this macro in both the page and the sidebar is consistently different.
For example, by using the Livesearch directly in a page, as the user types, search results are shown in a dropdown menu.
The same behaviour does not occurs in the macro if it's located in the sidebar.

h3. Environment
Confluence 6.0.0-OD-2015

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Refer to the space "Space Tools" > "Look and Feel";
# Sidebar, header and footer;
# Add the following code in the Sidebar section:
{code}
{livesearch:spaceKey="exp"}
{code}
change the spaceKey accordingly.

h3. Expected Results
The Livesearch macro will appear in the sidebar.
As the user types in, search results should be shown.

h3. Actual Results
The Livesearch appears.
The user types and no search suggestions are made.
